TY  - JOUR
AU  - Cremers, K. J. Martijn
AU  - Huang, Rocco
AU  - Sautner, Zacharias
T1  - Internal Capital Markets and Corporate Politics in a Banking Group
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhq121
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 24
IS  - 2
SP  - 358
EP  - 401
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We analyze proprietary internal capital allocation data from a large retail banking group consisting of member banks and a headquarters organization. We find that capital allocations from headquarters compensate for deposit shortfalls on the bank level, suggesting that the headquarters offers deposit smoothing to member banks. We then analyze how the distribution of influence within the group relates to capital allocations and lending behavior. More influential banks are allocated more funds from headquarters, and their loan growth is less sensitive to their deposit base. The effects of influence are stronger if banks have a greater demand for deposit smoothing.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhq121
ER  - 



